============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is a programming language?
A1: A programming language is a formal set of instructions
     for computers. High-level languages (Python, Java) are
     human-readable; low-level (Assembly) are closer to
     machine code.

Q2: What is evolution?
A2: Evolution by natural selection: organisms with
     beneficial traits reproduce more, passing traits to
     offspring. Over generations, populations change. Darwin
     proposed this in 1859.

Q3: What is the internet?
A3: The internet is a global network of interconnected
     computers using TCP/IP protocols. It began as ARPANET
     in 1969 and became public with the World Wide Web in
     1994.

Q4: What is the Magna Carta?
A4: The Magna Carta (1215) was a charter limiting royal
     power in England, establishing that the king is subject
     to law. It influenced modern constitutional law and
     human rights.

Q5: What is the periodic table?
A5: The periodic table organizes 118 elements by atomic
     number. Elements in the same column share chemical
     properties. Rows are periods; columns are groups.

